course_metadata.title: 6 Energy: Smart district scale management of energy systems

content_chunks.content: The study course introduces the structure of the heat and power system and electrical networks. Topics such as energy needs, energy demand profiles, and transmission and distribution networks will be covered. An overview of the energy districts on different scales will be provided, and the main principles of the energy market will be explained. The practical classes of the study course focus on the methods of problem-solving and their application using computer software. The content of the study course comprises thermal and electrical systems and network management, development and planning tasks and their most typical problem solutions. Within the study course, various aspects (criteria) are considered - technical, economic, quality, security of energy supply, market, ecological, social, information uncertainties and others.

Technology for smart energy district management and district-scale energy system optimization - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in energy system planning and electricity demand analysis using advanced heat demand assessment and energy resource evaluation methodologies. Students will master renewable energy integration strategies, sector coupling approaches, and transmission networks design for optimal distribution networks performance and smart grid technologies implementation. The curriculum focuses on practical energy market fundamentals understanding, energy infrastructure design principles, and energy flexibility management techniques for smart energy district applications. Participants will gain hands-on experience with energy economic analysis tools including net present value (NPV), internal rate of return (IRR), and key performance indicators (KPI) evaluation. The program emphasizes positive energy districts development, energy system modeling techniques, and energy scenario planning for comprehensive stakeholder engagement and energy sustainability assessment in modern energy systems.
